328272889.name: BLACK 60mm RING MAGNETS 60x13mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring

details.description_text: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 60x13mm Hole Size: 25mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Grade: Y35 Application: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc. Color: Black Magnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom plane Description: Ring Magnets Black- 60x13mmBLACK 60mm RING MAGNETS 60x13mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetThis ferrite ring magnet has an outside diameter of 50mm, an inside diameter of 25mm and a thickness of 10mm.Our ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 60x13mmHole Size: 25mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetGrade: Y35Application: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc.Color: BlackMagnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom planeFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. Only work with magnets using tools specially designed for magnets.Never keep magnets in close proximity to electrical equipment like mobile phones, computers, loudspeakers, hearing aids, pacemakers, etc.

details.description_text: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 40x6mm Hole Size: 22mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Color: Black Description: 5Pcs-Ring Magnets Black- 40x6mmBLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x6mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetThis ferrite ring magnet has an outside diameter of 40mm, an inside diameter of 22mm and a thickness of 6mm.Our ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 40x6mmHole Size: 22mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetColor: BlackFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. Only work with magnets using tools specially designed for magnets.Never keep magnets in close proximity to electrical equipment like mobile phones, computers, loudspeakers, hearing aids, pacemakers, etc.Package Include: 1x BLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x6mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent Magnet

Our ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture. A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized. Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors. Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components. Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces. Specifications: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 50x10mm Hole Size: 25mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Grade: Y35 Application: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc. Color: Black Magnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom plane Features: Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors. Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation. Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don't have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. Only work with magnets using tools specially designed for magnets. Never keep magnets in close proximity to electrical equipment like mobile phones, computers, loudspeakers, hearing aids, pacemakers, etc.

They boast of offering the highest energy product (of any material/magnets today) and are available in a wide variety of sizes, grades and shapes (discs, arcs, blocks, spheres, trapezoid etc.).NdFeB magnets are used in making many tools/equipment such as communication tools, computer devices, motors, sensors, speakers and medical treatment instruments just to mention a few tools/equipment.Rare earth neodymium magnets, also known as NdFeB magnets or Neo magnets, are made from an alloy of neodymium, iron and boron. They have excellent magnetic property and are extremely strong for their small size. Neodymium magnets are permanent, and have a high maximum magnetic energy.Due to high ratio of performance over price, neodymium magnets has become extremely popular in almost all applications that require high performance magnets such as motors, sensors, computers, communications, medical equipment, meters, home appliances, craft model, jewelry and so on.Powerful Permanent Magnets: Neodymium is a kind of rare earth metal, it’s suitable for making permanent & powerful magnets. This magnet has permanent magnetism, it will be the same powerful even decades after. Constructed of a super strong neodymium block magnet embedded in a steel channel. Magnet is recessed inside the steel channel for protection and added holding power.Application: Useful neodymium magnets for holding, mounting, home improvement, DIY projects, and many more. Great as a cabinet or shower door catcher.Best Coating Available: Ni+ Cu+ Ni triple layer coated. The best coating available, which provides a shiny and rust resistant protection for the magnets.MAGNETS COATED: The magnets are made from the very strong neodymium-iron-boron alloy (NdFeB) and have a stylish nickel coating (Ni-Cu-Ni) with an appealing silver surface.Grade N52: The Strongest Grade Available and therefore Stronger Than Any Comparable Products of a Lower Grade such as N35, N42, N45, N48.MULTIPLE USES :These Magnets are Ideal for DIY Purposes, as Refrigerator Magnets, Science Project Magnets, at Work or in the Office, for Scientific Purposes, for Arts and Crafts or in the Classroom at School.Personality & beautiful: Good Choice for your DIY projects, useful item for offices, home, etc .the uses is endless. Beyond your imagination！Specifications: Super Strong Grade N52 Neodymium MagnetsPlating /Coating: Ni-Cu-Ni (Nickel)Stronger than N42, N45, N48,N50 etc.Ni+ Cu+ Ni Heavy Duty PlatingTolerance: +/- 0.1Material: Neodymium Magnets (NdFeB)Magnetization Direction: through thicknessMax Operating Temp: 176ºF (80ºC)Ages:7+ ages, both for kids and adultsOuter Dia: 15mmHole Dia: 5.2mmThickness: 3mmShape: Disc Type With Counter Shank holeUsage:Acoustic field: the speaker, receiver, microphone, alarm, stage audio, car audio and so on.Electronics: permanent magnetic actuator vacuum circuit breakers, magnetic relays, meter, sound meter, a reed switch, sensors.Electrical field: VCM, CD / DVD-ROM, generators, motors, servo motors, micro-motors, motors, vibration motors.Machinery and equipment: magnetic separation, magnetic crane, magnetic machinery.Healthcare: MRI scanners, medical equipment, magnetic health products and so on.Wedding corsage badges, etc., can be replaced with a magnet attractsevery other clothes pins, so as not to damage the dress.For the overlying metal drawing board for fixing the drawing paper. Magnetic blackboard whiteboard fixed file drawings.Advertising magnets available to replace the original fixtures, at any time convenient to replace the ad content.Models piling, you can use small magnets to connect two widgets.Studio, bulk magnet can be used to adsorb screws and other parts, even wrenches and other toolsSafety Warning About Handling Neodymium Magnets:-Handling strong magnets in a proper manner is necessary to prevent personal injury and property damage, which include magnet damage.These magnets are not toys. Please do not give neodymium magnets to children under 3 years old. Small magnets pose a choking hazard, and can be lethal if swallowed. In addition, large magnets can easily pinch fingers. So always supervise children when playing with magnets and be sure they are aware of the dangers involved.Please keep magnets away from people who are wearing pacemakers or other medical devices. These magnets could also damage CRT monitors and TV’s.It is recommended to wear gloves when handling magnets.Always handle magnets individually. Do not handle multiple magnets at the same time unless they are widely separated or stacked together.When placing magnets together, place a spacing material between them such as a piece of plastic, wood or cardboard so that they are easy to separate when needed.Maintain a distance of at least 3 feet from other magnets or magnetically susceptible items when handling the magnets. Pay particular attention to scissors, knives, screw drivers or any other sharp metal objects.To separate one magnet from the others, place them on a durable non-metal surface with the magnet-to-be-separated hanging off the edge of the table.

They have excellent magnetic property and are extremely strong for their small size. Neodymium magnets are permanent, and have a high maximum magnetic energy.Due to high ratio of performance over price, neodymium magnets has become extremely popular in almost all applications that require high performance magnets such as motors, sensors, computers, communications, medical equipment, meters, home appliances, craft model, jewelry and so on.Powerful Permanent Magnets: Neodymium is a kind of rare earth metal, it’s suitable for making permanent & powerful magnets. This magnet has permanent magnetism, it will be the same powerful even decades after. Constructed of a super strong neodymium block magnet embedded in a steel channel. Magnet is recessed inside the steel channel for protection and added holding power.Application: Useful neodymium magnets for holding, mounting, home improvement, DIY projects, and many more. Great as a cabinet or shower door catcher.Best Coating Available: Ni+ Cu+ Ni triple layer coated. The best coating available, which provides a shiny and rust resistant protection for the magnets.MAGNETS COATED: The magnets are made from the very strong neodymium-iron-boron alloy (NdFeB) and have a stylish nickel coating (Ni-Cu-Ni) with an appealing silver surface.Grade N52: The Strongest Grade Available and therefore Stronger Than Any Comparable Products of a Lower Grade such as N35, N42, N45, N48.MULTIPLE USES :These Magnets are Ideal for DIY Purposes, as Refrigerator Magnets, Science Project Magnets, at Work or in the Office, for Scientific Purposes, for Arts and Crafts or in the Classroom at School.Personality & beautiful: Good Choice for your DIY projects, useful item for offices, home, etc .the uses is endless. Magnetic blackboard whiteboard fixed file drawings.Advertising magnets available to replace the original fixtures, at any time convenient to replace the ad content.Models piling, you can use small magnets to connect two widgets.Studio, bulk magnet can be used to adsorb screws and other parts, even wrenches and other toolsSafety Warning About Handling Neodymium Magnets:Handling strong magnets in a proper manner is necessary to prevent personal injury and property damage, which include magnet damage.These magnets are not toys. Please do not give neodymium magnets to children under 3 years old. Small magnets pose a choking hazard, and can be lethal if swallowed. In addition, large magnets can easily pinch fingers. So always supervise children when playing with magnets and be sure they are aware of the dangers involved.Please keep magnets away from people who are wearing pacemakers or other medical devices. These magnets could also damage CRT monitors and TV’s.It is recommended to wear gloves when handling magnets.Always handle magnets individually. Do not handle multiple magnets at the same time unless they are widely separated or stacked together.When placing magnets together, place a spacing material between them such as a piece of plastic, wood or cardboard so that they are easy to separate when needed.Maintain a distance of at least 3 feet from other magnets or magnetically susceptible items when handling the magnets. Pay particular attention to scissors, knives, screw drivers or any other sharp metal objects.To separate one magnet from the others, place them on a durable non-metal surface with the magnet-to-be-separated hanging off the edge of the table.

They boast of offering the highest energy product (of any material/magnets today) and are available in a wide variety of sizes, grades and shapes (discs, arcs, blocks, spheres, trapezoid etc.).NdFeB magnets are used in making many tools/equipment such as communication tools, computer devices, motors, sensors, speakers and medical treatment instruments just to mention a few tools/equipment.Rare earth neodymium magnets, also known as NdFeB magnets or Neo magnets, are made from an alloy of neodymium, iron and boron. They have excellent magnetic property and are extremely strong for their small size. Neodymium magnets are permanent, and have a high maximum magnetic energy.Due to high ratio of performance over price, neodymium magnets has become extremely popular in almost all applications that require high performance magnets such as motors, sensors, computers, communications, medical equipment, meters, home appliances, craft model, jewelry and so on.Powerful Permanent Magnets: Neodymium is a kind of rare earth metal, it's suitable for making permanent & powerful magnets. This magnet has permanent magnetism, it will be the same powerful even decades after. Constructed of a super strong neodymium block magnet embedded in a steel channel. Magnet is recessed inside the steel channel for protection and added holding power.Application: Useful neodymium magnets for holding, mounting, home improvement, DIY projects, and many more. Great as a cabinet or shower door catcher.Best Coating Available: Ni+ Cu+ Ni triple layer coated. Please do not give neodymium magnets to children under 3 years old. Small magnets pose a choking hazard, and can be lethal if swallowed. In addition, large magnets can easily pinch fingers. So always supervise children when playing with magnets and be sure they are aware of the dangers involved.Please keep magnets away from people who are wearing pacemakers or other medical devices. These magnets could also damage CRT monitors and TV’s.It is recommended to wear gloves when handling magnets.Always handle magnets individually. Do not handle multiple magnets at the same time unless they are widely separated or stacked together.When placing magnets together, place a spacing material between them such as a piece of plastic, wood or cardboard so that they are easy to separate when needed.Maintain a distance of at least 3 feet from other magnets or magnetically susceptible items when handling the magnets. Pay particular attention to scissors, knives, screw drivers or any other sharp metal objects.To separate one magnet from the others, place them on a durable non-metal surface with the magnet-to-be-separated hanging off the edge of the table.Package Include:1x 15x4x2mm Rectangular Neodymium Magnet 15x4x2mm Industrial Super Strong Neodymium Magnets Super Strength Permanent Magnet For Garage Craft Art

314259819.name: BLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x8mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent Magnet 40mm

details.description_text: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 40x8mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Application: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc. Color: Black Magnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom plane Size may be little bit Plus Minus Description: Ring Magnets BlackBLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x8mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetOur ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 40x8mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetApplication: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc.Color: BlackMagnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom planeSize may be little bit Plus MinusFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. Only work with magnets using tools specially designed for magnets.Never keep magnets in close proximity to electrical equipment like mobile phones, computers, loudspeakers, hearing aids, pacemakers, etc.সাইজ একটু কম বেশি হতে পারে

Please do not give neodymium magnets to children under 3 years old. Small magnets pose a choking hazard, and can be lethal if swallowed. In addition, large magnets can easily pinch fingers. So always supervise children when playing with magnets and be sure they are aware of the dangers involved.Please keep magnets away from people who are wearing pacemakers or other medical devices. These magnets could also damage CRT monitors and TV’s.It is recommended to wear gloves when handling magnets.Always handle magnets individually. Do not handle multiple magnets at the same time unless they are widely separated or stacked together.When placing magnets together, place a spacing material between them such as a piece of plastic, wood or cardboard so that they are easy to separate when needed.Maintain a distance of at least 3 feet from other magnets or magnetically susceptible items when handling the magnets. details.description_text: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 60x13mm Hole Size: 25mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Grade: Y35 Application: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc. Color: Black Magnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom plane Description: Ring Magnets Black- 60x13mmBLACK 60mm RING MAGNETS 60x13mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetThis ferrite ring magnet has an outside diameter of 50mm, an inside diameter of 25mm and a thickness of 10mm.Our ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 60x13mmHole Size: 25mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetGrade: Y35Application: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc.Color: BlackMagnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom planeFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. Only work with magnets using tools specially designed for magnets.Never keep magnets in close proximity to electrical equipment like mobile phones, computers, loudspeakers, hearing aids, pacemakers, etc.

details.description_text: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 40x8mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Application: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc. Color: Black Magnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom plane Size may be little bit Plus Minus #magnet Description: Ring Magnets BlackBLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x8mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetOur ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 40x8mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetApplication: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc.Color: BlackMagnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom planeSize may be little bit Plus MinusFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. Only work with magnets using tools specially designed for magnets.Never keep magnets in close proximity to electrical equipment like mobile phones, computers, loudspeakers, hearing aids, pacemakers, etc.সাইজ একটু কম বেশি হতে পারে

They boast of offering the highest energy product (of any material/magnets today) and are available in a wide variety of sizes, grades and shapes (discs, arcs, blocks, spheres, trapezoid etc.).NdFeB magnets are used in making many tools/equipment such as communication tools, computer devices, motors, sensors, speakers and medical treatment instruments just to mention a few tools/equipment.Rare earth neodymium magnets, also known as NdFeB magnets or Neo magnets, are made from an alloy of neodymium, iron and boron. Please do not give neodymium magnets to children under 3 years old. Small magnets pose a choking hazard, and can be lethal if swallowed. In addition, large magnets can easily pinch fingers. So always supervise children when playing with magnets and be sure they are aware of the dangers involved.Please keep magnets away from people who are wearing pacemakers or other medical devices. These magnets could also damage CRT monitors and TV’s.It is recommended to wear gloves when handling magnets.Always handle magnets individually. Do not handle multiple magnets at the same time unless they are widely separated or stacked together.When placing magnets together, place a spacing material between them such as a piece of plastic, wood or cardboard so that they are easy to separate when needed.Maintain a distance of at least 3 feet from other magnets or magnetically susceptible items when handling the magnets. details.description_text: The Neodymium magnet is a permanent magnet made from an alloy of neodymium, iron and boron. NdFeB magnet are widely used in various fields, such as motors, speakers, electric generators etc. Besides, neodymium magnet is the strongest type of permanent magnet commercially available.The Neodymium (chemical symbol Nd) is element 60 on the periodic table. It is a rare earth metal and forms one of the Lanthanides series. When added to Iron (Fe) and Boron (B) (chemical formula Nd14Fe21B) the resultant magnets are the strongest magnets currently available. Neodymium magnets are sometimes known as Neo, Neod or NIB magnets.The Neodymium magnets are usually coated Nickel-Copper-Nickel plating to prevent the iron from rusting. Neodymium magnets are made of a brittle material. These magnets are not as strong as steel. They are more like a brittle ceramic. If you let two magnets slam together, they can crack and break. This is true for magnets large and small. Warning: These magnets are very powerful which should be handled with great care. Children should not be allowed to handle neodymium magnets, as they can be dangerous. These magnets are not toys. Small magnets risk a chocking hazard and should never be swallowed or inserted into any part of the body. Never allow neodymium magnets near a person with a pacemaker or similar medical devices. The strong magnetic fields can affect the operation of such devices.Specifications:Dimensions 25mm diameter x 2mm thickness, (0.984in x 0.078in) 63/64in x 5/64inTolerances ±0.05mm x ±0.05mmPull Force (approx.) Magnet to a Steel Plate : 10.11 LB, Between 2 Steel Plates : 65.25 LB, Magnet to Magnet : 10.11 LBMaterial NdFeB, Grade N52Shape Round DiscPlating/Coating Ni-Cu-Ni (Nickel)Magnetization Direction Axial (Poles on Flat Ends)Surface Gauss (approx.) 2,610 GaussMax Operating Temperature 176ºF (80ºC)Brmax 14,800 GaussWeight 11 gramsPacking List:1Pc * 25*2mm with 3M adhesive N35 magnet

details.description_text: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 45x8mm Hole Size: 19mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Color: Black Magnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom plane Description: Ring Magnets Black- 45x8mmBLACK 45mm RING MAGNETS 45x8mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetThis ferrite ring magnet has an outside diameter of 50mm, an inside diameter of 25mm and a thickness of 8mm.Our ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 45x8mmHole Size: 19mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetColor: BlackMagnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom planeFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. 530384941.name: 5Pcs- Ring Magnet 40x6mm Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent Magnet

details.description_text: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 40x6mm Hole Size: 22mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Color: Black Description: 5Pcs-Ring Magnets Black- 40x6mmBLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x6mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetThis ferrite ring magnet has an outside diameter of 40mm, an inside diameter of 22mm and a thickness of 6mm.Our ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 40x6mmHole Size: 22mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetColor: BlackFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. Only work with magnets using tools specially designed for magnets.Never keep magnets in close proximity to electrical equipment like mobile phones, computers, loudspeakers, hearing aids, pacemakers, etc.Package Include: 1x BLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x6mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent Magnet

One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 40x8mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetApplication: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc.Color: BlackMagnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom planeSize may be little bit Plus MinusFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. details.description_text: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 60x13mm Hole Size: 25mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Grade: Y35 Application: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc. Color: Black Magnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom plane Description: Ring Magnets Black- 60x13mmBLACK 60mm RING MAGNETS 60x13mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetThis ferrite ring magnet has an outside diameter of 50mm, an inside diameter of 25mm and a thickness of 10mm.Our ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 60x13mmHole Size: 25mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetGrade: Y35Application: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc.Color: BlackMagnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom planeFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. Only work with magnets using tools specially designed for magnets.Never keep magnets in close proximity to electrical equipment like mobile phones, computers, loudspeakers, hearing aids, pacemakers, etc.Package Include: 1x BLACK 60mm RING MAGNETS 60x13mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent Magnet

details.description_text: Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring Magnet Size: 40x6mm Hole Size: 22mm Shape: Ring Material: Ferrite Magnet Color: Black Description: 5Pcs-Ring Magnets Black- 40x6mmBLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x6mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetThis ferrite ring magnet has an outside diameter of 40mm, an inside diameter of 22mm and a thickness of 6mm.Our ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 40x6mmHole Size: 22mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetColor: BlackFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250°C and down to -40°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they don’t have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. Only work with magnets using tools specially designed for magnets.Never keep magnets in close proximity to electrical equipment like mobile phones, computers, loudspeakers, hearing aids, pacemakers, etc.Package Include: 1x BLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x6mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent Magnet

details.description_text: Super Strong Grade N52 Neodymium Magnets Plating /Coating: Ni-Cu-Ni (Nickel) Stronger than N42, N45, N48,N50 etc. Ni+ Cu+ Ni Heavy Duty Plating Tolerance: +/- 0.1 Material: Neodymium Magnets (NdFeB) Magnetization Direction: through thickness Max Operating Temp: 176ºF (80ºC) Ages:7+ ages, both for kids and adults Hole Dia: 10mm Thickness: 1mm Shape: Disc Type With Counter Shank hole Description: Disc Neodymium Magnet 10x1mm Super Strong Bar Magnets 10×1mm Magnet DISC Neodymium Magnet 10×1mm Industrial Super Strong 10mm Magnet Neodymium Magnets powerful Permanent MagnetNdFeB magnets (also known as “neo” magnets) are among the most popular magnets in the market today. They boast of offering the highest energy product (of any material/magnets today) and are available in a wide variety of sizes, grades and shapes (discs, arcs, blocks, spheres, trapezoid etc.).NdFeB magnets are used in making many tools/equipment such as communication tools, computer devices, motors, sensors, speakers and medical treatment instruments just to mention a few tools/equipment.Rare earth neodymium magnets, also known as NdFeB magnets or Neo magnets, are made from an alloy of neodymium, iron and boron. They have excellent magnetic property and are extremely strong for their small size. Neodymium magnets are permanent, and have a high maximum magnetic energy.Due to high ratio of performance over price, neodymium magnets has become extremely popular in almost all applications that require high performance magnets such as motors, sensors, computers, communications, medical equipment, meters, home appliances, craft model, jewelry and so on.Powerful Permanent Magnets: Neodymium is a kind of rare earth metal, it’s suitable for making permanent & powerful magnets. This magnet has permanent magnetism, it will be the same powerful even decades after. Constructed of a super strong neodymium block magnet embedded in a steel channel. Magnet is recessed inside the steel channel for protection and added holding power.Application: Useful neodymium magnets for holding, mounting, home improvement, DIY projects, and many more. Great as a cabinet or shower door catcher.Best Coating Available: Ni+ Cu+ Ni triple layer coated. The best coating available, which provides a shiny and rust resistant protection for the magnets.MAGNETS COATED: The magnets are made from the very strong neodymium-iron-boron alloy (NdFeB) and have a stylish nickel coating (Ni-Cu-Ni) with an appealing silver surface.Grade N52: The Strongest Grade Available and therefore Stronger Than Any Comparable Products of a Lower Grade such as N35, N42, N45, N48.MULTIPLE USES :These Magnets are Ideal for DIY Purposes, as Refrigerator Magnets, Science Project Magnets, at Work or in the Office, for Scientific Purposes, for Arts and Crafts or in the Classroom at School.Personality & beautiful: Good Choice for your DIY projects, useful item for offices, home, etc .the uses is endless. Beyond your imagination！Specifications: Super Strong Grade N52 Neodymium MagnetsPlating /Coating: Ni-Cu-Ni (Nickel)Stronger than N42, N45, N48,N50 etc.Ni+ Cu+ Ni Heavy Duty PlatingTolerance: +/- 0.1Material: Neodymium Magnets (NdFeB)Magnetization Direction: through thicknessMax Operating Temp: 176ºF (80ºC)Ages:7+ ages, both for kids and adultsHole Dia: 10mmThickness: 1mmShape: Disc Type With Counter Shank holeUsage:Acoustic field: the speaker, receiver, microphone, alarm, stage audio, car audio and so on.Electronics: permanent magnetic actuator vacuum circuit breakers, magnetic relays, meter, sound meter, a reed switch, sensors.Electrical field: VCM, CD / DVD-ROM, generators, motors, servo motors, micro-motors, motors, vibration motors.Machinery and equipment: magnetic separation, magnetic crane, magnetic machinery.Healthcare: MRI scanners, medical equipment, magnetic health products and so on.Wedding corsage badges, etc., can be replaced with a magnet attractsevery other clothes pins, so as not to damage the dress.For the overlying metal drawing board for fixing the drawing paper. Magnetic blackboard whiteboard fixed file drawings.Advertising magnets available to replace the original fixtures, at any time convenient to replace the ad content.Models piling, you can use small magnets to connect two widgets.Studio, bulk magnet can be used to adsorb screws and other parts, even wrenches and other toolsSafety Warning About Handling Neodymium Magnets:Handling strong magnets in a proper manner is necessary to prevent personal injury and property damage, which include magnet damage.These magnets are not toys. Please do not give neodymium magnets to children under 3 years old. Small magnets pose a choking hazard, and can be lethal if swallowed. In addition, large magnets can easily pinch fingers. So always supervise children when playing with magnets and be sure they are aware of the dangers involved.Please keep magnets away from people who are wearing pacemakers or other medical devices. These magnets could also damage CRT monitors and TV’s.It is recommended to wear gloves when handling magnets.Always handle magnets individually. Do not handle multiple magnets at the same time unless they are widely separated or stacked together.When placing magnets together, place a spacing material between them such as a piece of plastic, wood or cardboard so that they are easy to separate when needed.Maintain a distance of at least 3 feet from other magnets or magnetically susceptible items when handling the magnets. Pay particular attention to scissors, knives, screw drivers or any other sharp metal objects.To separate one magnet from the others, place them on a durable non-metal surface with the magnet-to-be-separated hanging off the edge of the table.

Color: Black Magnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom plane Size may be little bit Plus Minus Description: Ring Magnets BlackBLACK 40mm RING MAGNETS 40x8mm Ring Magnets Multipurpose Permanent Round Ring Magnet Permanent MagnetOur ferrite ring magnets are often used in loudspeakers and also in resonance imaging and torque drives. One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize. They are used to make permanent magnets for applications such as refrigerator magnets, loudspeakers, and small electric motors.Soft ferrite have low coercive, so they easily change their magnetization and act as conductors of magnetic fields. They are used in the electronics industry to make efficient magnetic cores called ferrite cores for high-frequency inductors and transformers, and in various microwave components.Ferrite compounds are extremely low cost, being made of mostly rusted iron (iron oxide), and have excellent corrosion resistance. They are very stable and difficult to demagnetize, and can be made with both high and low coercive forces.Specifications:Name: Ring Shaped Ferrite Ring MagnetSize: 40x8mmShape: RingMaterial: Ferrite MagnetApplication: Speaker, Sensors, Separators, Microwaves Etc.Color: BlackMagnetization Direction: N S pole on top and bottom planeSize may be little bit Plus MinusFeatures:Ferrite ring magnets withstand temperatures of up to 250Â°C and down to -40Â°C and can therefore be used both indoors and outdoors.Magnets should always be kept away from small children due to the risk of suffocation.Ferrite magnets are a bit fragile as they donâ€™t have a protective coating. Avoid bumps and knocks. details.description_text: Super Strong Grade N52 Neodymium Magnets Plating /Coating: Ni-Cu-Ni (Nickel) Stronger than N42, N45, N48,N50 etc. Ni+ Cu+ Ni Heavy Duty Plating Tolerance: +/- 0.1 Material: Neodymium Magnets (NdFeB) Magnetization Direction: through thickness Max Operating Temp: 176ºF (80ºC) Ages:7+ ages, both for kids and adults Outer Dia: 30mm Hole Dia: 7mm Thickness: 5mm Shape: Disc Type With Counter Shank hole Description: Disc Neodymium Magnet 30x5mm With Countersunk Hole Industrial NdFeB N42 MagnetDisc Neodymium Magnet 30x5mm With Countersunk Hole Industrial Super Strong Rare Earth Neodymium Bar Magnets Super Strength Permanent NdFeB N42 Magnet For Garage Science ProjectsNdFeB magnets (also known as “neo” magnets) are among the most popular magnets in the market today. They boast of offering the highest energy product (of any material/magnets today) and are available in a wide variety of sizes, grades and shapes (discs, arcs, blocks, spheres, trapezoid etc.).NdFeB magnets are used in making many tools/equipment such as communication tools, computer devices, motors, sensors, speakers and medical treatment instruments just to mention a few tools/equipment.Rare earth neodymium magnets, also known as NdFeB magnets or Neo magnets, are made from an alloy of neodymium, iron and boron. They have excellent magnetic property and are extremely strong for their small size. Neodymium magnets are permanent, and have a high maximum magnetic energy.Due to high ratio of performance over price, neodymium magnets has become extremely popular in almost all applications that require high performance magnets such as motors, sensors, computers, communications, medical equipment, meters, home appliances, craft model, jewelry and so on.Powerful Permanent Magnets: Neodymium is a kind of rare earth metal, it’s suitable for making permanent & powerful magnets. This magnet has permanent magnetism, it will be the same powerful even decades after. Constructed of a super strong neodymium block magnet embedded in a steel channel. Magnet is recessed inside the steel channel for protection and added holding power.Application: Useful neodymium magnets for holding, mounting, home improvement, DIY projects, and many more. Great as a cabinet or shower door catcher.Best Coating Available: Ni+ Cu+ Ni triple layer coated. The best coating available, which provides a shiny and rust resistant protection for the magnets.MAGNETS COATED: The magnets are made from the very strong neodymium-iron-boron alloy (NdFeB) and have a stylish nickel coating (Ni-Cu-Ni) with an appealing silver surface.Grade N52: The Strongest Grade Available and therefore Stronger Than Any Comparable Products of a Lower Grade such as N35, N42, N45, N48.MULTIPLE USES :These Magnets are Ideal for DIY Purposes, as Refrigerator Magnets, Science Project Magnets, at Work or in the Office, for Scientific Purposes, for Arts and Crafts or in the Classroom at School.Personality & beautiful: Good Choice for your DIY projects, useful item for offices, home, etc .the uses is endless. Beyond your imagination！Specifications: Super Strong Grade N52 Neodymium MagnetsPlating /Coating: Ni-Cu-Ni (Nickel)Stronger than N42, N45, N48,N50 etc.Ni+ Cu+ Ni Heavy Duty PlatingTolerance: +/- 0.1Material: Neodymium Magnets (NdFeB)Magnetization Direction: through thicknessMax Operating Temp: 176ºF (80ºC)Ages:7+ ages, both for kids and adultsOuter Dia: 30mmHole Dia: 7mmThickness: 5mmShape: Disc Type With Counter Shank holeUsage:Acoustic field: the speaker, receiver, microphone, alarm, stage audio, car audio and so on.Electronics: permanent magnetic actuator vacuum circuit breakers, magnetic relays, meter, sound meter, a reed switch, sensors.Electrical field: VCM, CD / DVD-ROM, generators, motors, servo motors, micro-motors, motors, vibration motors.Machinery and equipment: magnetic separation, magnetic crane, magnetic machinery.Healthcare: MRI scanners, medical equipment, magnetic health products and so on.Wedding corsage badges, etc., can be replaced with a magnet attractsevery other clothes pins, so as not to damage the dress.For the overlying metal drawing board for fixing the drawing paper. Magnetic blackboard whiteboard fixed file drawings.Advertising magnets available to replace the original fixtures, at any time convenient to replace the ad content.Models piling, you can use small magnets to connect two widgets.Studio, bulk magnet can be used to adsorb screws and other parts, even wrenches and other toolsSafety Warning About Handling Neodymium Magnets:-Handling strong magnets in a proper manner is necessary to prevent personal injury and property damage, which include magnet damage.These magnets are not toys. Please do not give neodymium magnets to children under 3 years old. Small magnets pose a choking hazard, and can be lethal if swallowed. In addition, large magnets can easily pinch fingers. So always supervise children when playing with magnets and be sure they are aware of the dangers involved.Please keep magnets away from people who are wearing pacemakers or other medical devices. These magnets could also damage CRT monitors and TV’s.It is recommended to wear gloves when handling magnets.Always handle magnets individually. Do not handle multiple magnets at the same time unless they are widely separated or stacked together.When placing magnets together, place a spacing material between them such as a piece of plastic, wood or cardboard so that they are easy to separate when needed.Maintain a distance of at least 3 feet from other magnets or magnetically susceptible items when handling the magnets. Pay particular attention to scissors, knives, screw drivers or any other sharp metal objects.To separate one magnet from the others, place them on a durable non-metal surface with the magnet-to-be-separated hanging off the edge of the table.Package Include:1x Disc Neodymium Magnet 30x5mm With Countersunk Hole Industrial Super Strong Rare Earth Neodymium Bar Magnets Super Strength Permanent NdFeB N42 Magnet For Garage Science Projects
